This paper is about optimizing a high-performance distributed memory implementation of the Markov Cluster Algorithm (MCL) for large-scale networks. The paper focuses on improving the scalability and performance of the algorithm, which suggests that it belongs to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper heavily relies on sparse matrix computations, which suggests that it could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Other likely sub-categories include Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), Databases (cs.DB), and Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE), as the paper involves developing new algorithms and optimizations for clustering large-scale networks.
